<project xml:id="cool-dondeEstanLosRectangulos" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>¿Dónde están los rectángulos?</title>

<statement>
  <p>Encuentra el área de esta figura. Explica o muestra tu razonamiento.</p>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151025">
        <shortdescription>Figura en forma de T compuesta por cuadrados unitarios.</shortdescription>
      </image>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>54 square units. Sample response: I split the figure into 2 rectangles, 1 across the top and 1 below. I found the area of the rectangle across the top by multiplying <m>3 \times 10</m>, which is 30. I found the area of the bottom rectangle by multiplying <m>4 \times 6</m>, which is 24. Then, I added the area of both rectangles to get 54.</p>
  </solution>


